@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<style>
    /* Light mode defaults */
    .privacy-card {
        background-color: #fff;
        border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
    }
    
    .privacy-card .card-body {
        color: #212529;
    }
    
    .privacy-card h2,
    .privacy-card h3,
    .privacy-card h4,
    .privacy-card h5 {
        color: #212529;
    }
    
    /* Dark mode - using data-theme attribute */
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card {
        background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    }
    
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card .card-body,
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card .card-body p,
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card .card-body ul,
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card .card-body li,
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card .card-body strong {
        color: #e9ecef !important;
    }
    
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card h2,
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card h3,
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card h4,
    [data-theme="dark"] .privacy-card h5 {
        color: #f8f9fa !important;
    }
    
    [data-theme="dark"] .alert-info {
        background-color: rgba(13, 110, 253, 0.2);
        border-color: rgba(13, 110, 253, 0.3);
        color: #e9ecef !important;
    }
    
    [data-theme="dark"] .alert-info ul,
    [data-theme="dark"] .alert-info li,
    [data-theme="dark"] .alert-info p,
    [data-theme="dark"] .alert-info h3 {
        color: #e9ecef !important;
    }
    
    [data-theme="dark"] .text-muted {
        color: #adb5bd !important;
    }
    
    [data-theme="dark"] .container h1 {
        color: #f8f9fa !important;
    }
    
    /* Dark mode - using prefers-color-scheme as fallback */
    @@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
        .privacy-card {
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        }
        
        .privacy-card .card-body,
        .privacy-card .card-body p,
        .privacy-card .card-body ul,
        .privacy-card .card-body li,
        .privacy-card .card-body strong {
            color: #e9ecef !important;
        }
        
        .privacy-card h2,
        .privacy-card h3,
        .privacy-card h4,
        .privacy-card h5 {
            color: #f8f9fa !important;
        }
        
        .alert-info {
            background-color: rgba(13, 110, 253, 0.2);
            border-color: rgba(13, 110, 253, 0.3);
            color: #e9ecef !important;
        }
        
        .alert-info ul,
        .alert-info li,
        .alert-info p,
        .alert-info h3 {
            color: #e9ecef !important;
        }
        
        .text-muted {
            color: #adb5bd !important;
        }
        
        .container h1 {
            color: #f8f9fa !important;
        }
    }
</style>

<div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="mb-4">Privacy Policy for Briefed</h1>
    <p class="text-muted"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> December 27, 2025</p>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                Welcome to Briefed ("we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, 
                and safeguard your information when you use our RSS feed reader application and related services (collectively, the "Service").
            </p>
            <p>
                By using Briefed, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>
            
            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">2.1 Personal Information</h3>
            <p>When you register for an account, we collect:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Email address:</strong> Used for account authentication and communication</li>
                <li><strong>Password:</strong> Encrypted and stored securely for account access</li>
                <li><strong>Account creation date:</strong> For record-keeping purposes</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">2.2 Content and Usage Data</h3>
            <p>When you use the Service, we collect:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>RSS feed subscriptions:</strong> URLs and metadata of feeds you subscribe to</li>
                <li><strong>Reading history:</strong> Articles you've read, marked as read, or saved</li>
                <li><strong>Content reports:</strong> When you report AI-generated content as inaccurate or inappropriate</li>
                <li><strong>Preferences:</strong> Your app settings and customization choices</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">2.3 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Log data:</strong> IP address, browser type, access times, and pages viewed</li>
                <li><strong>Device information:</strong> Device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers (for mobile app)</li>
                <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Session cookies for authentication and functionality</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the collected information for:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Service provision:</strong> To provide, maintain, and improve the Briefed service</li>
                <li><strong>Account management:</strong> To create and manage your account</li>
                <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> To customize your feed experience and remember your preferences</li>
                <li><strong>AI features:</strong> To generate article summaries and fact-checking results</li>
                <li><strong>Content moderation:</strong> To review and respond to reported content</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> To understand usage patterns and improve our service</li>
                <li><strong>Security:</strong> To detect, prevent, and address technical issues and unauthorized access</li>
                <li><strong>Legal compliance:</strong> To comply with legal obligations and protect our rights</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">4. AI-Generated Content</h2>
            <p>
                Briefed uses artificial intelligence to generate article summaries and perform fact-checking. 
                This is done using local AI models (Ollama) or third-party AI services (Groq).
            </p>
            
            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">4.1 AI Data Processing</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Article content is processed by AI to generate summaries</li>
                <li>AI-generated content is clearly labeled as such</li>
                <li>You can report AI-generated content that appears misleading, inaccurate, or inappropriate</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">4.2 Third-Party AI Services</h3>
            <p>When using third-party AI services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Article content may be sent to external AI providers for processing</li>
                <li>These providers have their own privacy policies and data handling practices</li>
                <li>We select providers that comply with data protection standards</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information only in the following circumstances:</p>
            
            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">5.1 Service Providers</h3>
            <p>We may share data with third-party service providers who assist us in:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Cloud hosting and infrastructure (servers, databases)</li>
                <li>AI processing services (for summaries and fact-checking)</li>
                <li>Analytics and performance monitoring</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">5.2 Legal Requirements</h3>
            <p>We may disclose your information if required to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Comply with legal obligations, court orders, or subpoenas</li>
                <li>Protect our rights, property, or safety</li>
                <li>Investigate fraud, security issues, or terms of service violations</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">5.3 Business Transfers</h3>
            <p>
                In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred 
                as part of that transaction, subject to the same privacy protections.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">6. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Passwords are hashed using industry-standard encryption</li>
                <li><strong>HTTPS:</strong> All data transmission is encrypted using SSL/TLS</li>
                <li><strong>Access controls:</strong> Limited access to personal data by authorized personnel only</li>
                <li><strong>Database security:</strong> Secure database configurations and regular backups</li>
                <li><strong>Monitoring:</strong> Regular security audits and monitoring for suspicious activity</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3">
                While we strive to protect your information, no method of transmission over the internet or 
                electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">7. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain your personal information for as long as:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Your account is active</li>
                <li>Needed to provide you with services</li>
                <li>Required to comply with legal obligations</li>
                <li>Necessary to resolve disputes and enforce our agreements</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3">
                When you delete your account, we will delete or anonymize your personal information 
                within 30 days, except where retention is required by law.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">8. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
            <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights:</p>
            
            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">8.1 Access and Portability</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Request a copy of your personal data</li>
                <li>Export your feed subscriptions and saved articles</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">8.2 Correction and Deletion</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Update your email address or password</li>
                <li>Delete your account and associated data</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">8.3 Control Over Content</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Choose which feeds to subscribe to</li>
                <li>Control which articles you read and save</li>
                <li>Report inappropriate AI-generated content</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">8.4 Communication Preferences</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Opt out of non-essential communications</li>
                <li>Manage cookie preferences through browser settings</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>
                Briefed is not intended for children under the age of 13 (or applicable age of digital consent in your country). 
                We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we learn we have collected information 
                from a child under 13, we will delete it promptly.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3">
                If you believe we have collected information from a child, please contact us immediately.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">10. International Data Transfers</h2>
            <p>
                Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. 
                These countries may have different data protection laws. By using Briefed, you consent to 
                the transfer of your information to these locations.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3">
                We take steps to ensure your information receives adequate protection wherever it is processed, 
                including through contractual safeguards and compliance with applicable frameworks.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">11. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>Briefed integrates with third-party services:</p>
            
            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">11.1 RSS Feed Sources</h3>
            <p>
                When you subscribe to RSS feeds, you're accessing content from third-party websites. 
                Those websites have their own privacy policies and terms of service.
            </p>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">11.2 AI Service Providers</h3>
            <p>AI features may use:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Ollama:</strong> Local AI processing (data stays on our servers)</li>
                <li><strong>Groq:</strong> Cloud-based AI service (subject to Groq's privacy policy)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">11.3 Fact-Checking Services</h3>
            <p>
                Fact-checking features may query external databases and APIs to verify claims. 
                These services have their own privacy policies.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">12. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
            <p>We use cookies and similar technologies:</p>
            
            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">12.1 Essential Cookies</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Authentication cookies:</strong> To keep you logged in</li>
                <li><strong>Security cookies:</strong> To protect against unauthorized access</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="h5 mt-4 mb-2">12.2 Functional Cookies</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Preference cookies:</strong> To remember your settings</li>
                <li><strong>Session cookies:</strong> To maintain your browsing session</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mt-3">
                You can control cookies through your browser settings, but disabling cookies may affect 
                the functionality of the Service.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
                <li>Notify you of significant changes via email or in-app notification</li>
                <li>Provide a reasonable notice period before the changes take effect</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3">
                Your continued use of Briefed after changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4 privacy-card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4 mb-3">14. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your personal information, please contact us:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Email:</strong> amedeo.vertullo@gmail.com</li>
                <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://briefed.step0fail.com">https://briefed.step0fail.com</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3">
                We will respond to your inquiry within 30 days.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="alert alert-info">
        <h3 class="h5 mb-3">📱 For Google Play Store Users</h3>
        <p class="mb-2">
            This app complies with Google Play's User Data policy, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="mb-0">
            <li>Prominent disclosure of data collection and use</li>
            <li>Secure transmission of sensitive data</li>
            <li>Clear labeling of AI-generated content</li>
            <li>User reporting mechanisms for AI content</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-5 pt-4 border-top">
        <p class="text-muted">
            <small>
                By using Briefed, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy 
                and agree to its terms.
            </small>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
